        <briefdescription>
<para>Detect and generate contacts for oriented box-box intersection. </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>Computes contact(s) between two oriented boxes using SAT.</para>
<para>Uses a Separating Axis Theorem (SAT) test and then builds a contact manifold for impulse-based solving.</para>
<para><parameterlist kind="param"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername direction="in">a</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>First box shape. </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername direction="in">ta</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para><ref refid="classnovaphy_1_1_world" kindref="compound">World</ref> transform of first box parent body. </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername direction="in">b</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Second box shape. </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername direction="in">tb</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para><ref refid="classnovaphy_1_1_world" kindref="compound">World</ref> transform of second box parent body. </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername direction="out">contacts</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Generated world-space contact manifold points. </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
<simplesect kind="return"><para>True if boxes overlap.</para>
</simplesect>
Tests 15 separating axes (face normals and edge cross products), then generates a compact face or edge contact set. <parameterlist kind="param"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername direction="in">a</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
